{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019ps3mtqj5xxZwseCppqUmf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that Elasticsearch 8.x requires transport SSL to be enabled when security is enabled. But we only have HTTP TLS certs, not transport TLS certs. Options:\n1. Enable transport SSL with the same certs (ca.crt, tls.crt, tls.key) - but transport SSL requires peer verification which needs proper hostname/IP SANs\n2. Disable security (`xpack.security.enabled: false`) - but then the password secret is irrelevant\n3. Use the same TLS certs for transport SSL too\nI'll go with the simplest approach: enabling transport SSL with the same certificate files and setting verification mode to certificate instead of requiring full hostname validation. Now I need to update the ConfigMap to add the transport SSL configuration.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":376,"cache_read_input_tokens":39401,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":376},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d71902a5-46a3-43f5-9cc6-dbc4b0146234","uuid":"32f8c7c0-fa32-4b80-a056-98447b2dfa82","request_id":"req_011CcMvAZusE9mG9sV3MiLgX"}
