{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014S6oKERZFxmXn2zdcAZmkK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working. Here's a summary of what was deployed:\n\n**Resources created:**\n- `ConfigMap/elasticsearch-config` — ES config with security + HTTP/transport TLS using the existing `es-http-tls` secret\n- `Service/elasticsearch-headless` — headless (ClusterIP: None) with `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` so nodes can discover each other via DNS before readiness passes\n- `Service/es-http` — ClusterIP service on port 9200 named as required\n- `StatefulSet/elasticsearch` — 3 replicas, `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` so all nodes start simultaneously, using `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` from the `elastic-password` secret\n- `PodDisruptionBudget/elasticsearch-pdb` — minAvailable: 2\n\n**Key issues resolved during deployment:**\n1. `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` is an env var (not a `elasticsearch.yml` key)\n2. ES 8.x requires transport SSL enabled when security is on — used the same `es-http-tls` certs for transport\n3. `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` prevents the deadlock where pod-0 can't be Ready without pod-1/2 and vice versa\n4. `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` on the headless service allows inter-node DNS resolution before pods pass readiness\n\n**Result:** 3-node cluster, status green, reads and writes confirmed through `es-http:9200` over HTTPS."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":387,"cache_read_input_tokens":56766,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":387},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d71902a5-46a3-43f5-9cc6-dbc4b0146234","uuid":"2739a075-3d4f-42ef-b15a-d9ae3606e865","request_id":"req_011CcMwoojUKYzHhrGA9U16s"}
